Package graph

Interface LabeledEdge<N extends Node<N,​E>,​E extends Edge<N,​E>,​L>

  • Type Parameters:
    N - The type of nodes in the graph
    E - The type of edges in the graph
    L - The type of labels on the edges
    All Superinterfaces:
    Edge<N,​E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Adapter.Edge, AdjacencyListGraph.Edge
    public interface LabeledEdge<N extends Node<N,​E>,​E extends Edge<N,​E>,​L>
extends Edge<N,​E>
    Labeled edges are edges that have a label associated with them (of type L). This interface is useful for specifying generic algorithms that require weighted edges. For example, Dijkstra's algorithm requires integer weights; this is apparent in the type of GraphAlgorithms.dijkstra: public static , E extends LabeledEdge> ... This means that dijkstra's can only be called if E is a LabeledEdge with integer lables.
